createredirect-error:
Unused at this time.

Used as error message.
createredirect-enable-multiline: Label for button that allows to enter multiple titles.
createredirect-instructions:
Used as instructions message.

This message is followed by the Redirect form.
createredirect-invalid-title:
Used as error message when incorrect title is entered.
* $1 is the title as entered by the user.
createredirect-overwrite: Used as label for checkbox that allows to overwrite existing pages.
createredirect-page-title:
Used as label for Original Title input box.
{{Identical|Page title}}
createredirect-redirect-done:
This message indicates the redirect $2 (from the page $1) has been created successfully.

Parameters:
* $1 - original title
* $2 - redirect title
createredirect-redirect-to: Used as label for Redirect Title input box.
createredirect-save:
Used as Submit button text.
{{Identical|Save page}}
createredirect-would-overwrite:
Used as error message when page $1 already exists (user is attempting to overwrite it with redirect).

Parameters:
* $1 - redirect title
